=head1 Prerequisites

=head2 System
=over
=item Ubuntu 11.10 or Ubuntu 12.04
=back

All packages are built and tested against Ubuntu 11.10 and 12.04. While its
entirely possible to run this software on any Linux distro, these instructions
are based on the assumption that you will be installing them on the above
mentioned system/version.

=head2 libiomeme-perl
=over
=item libimager-perl
=item libmoose-perl
=back

=head2 libiomeme-www
=over
=item nginx
=item libiomeme-perl
=item libmojolicious-perl
=item libcache-fastmmap-perl
=back

=head2 Building Packages
=over
=item make
=item fakeroot
=item dpkg-deb
=item dpkg
=back

=head1 Installation

=head2 libiomeme-perl
=pod
    cd libiomeme-perl/
    sudo make install
=cut

=head2 libiomeme-www
=pod
    cd libiomeme-www/
    sudo make install

    # The default nginx settings for iomeme listen on port 1337.
    # Update the "listen" parameter in /etc/nginx/sites-available/iomeme if
    # you want something else
=cut


=head1 Start services
=pod
    sudo service iomeme start
    sudo service nginx start
=cut


=head1 Try it out!
=pod
    http://localhost:1337/sk/installed+iomeme/it+works!
=cut
